From 7a0ab95be41f63dd17333cd636c36592ad07fb98 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jianhui Zhao <zhaojh329@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Sep 2025 09:07:58 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] fix(mqtt): Fix MQTT ping response timeout race condition

Reorder operations in ping timer callback to prevent a race condition
where the ping response could be received before the timeout timer was set.

Previously:
1. Send PINGREQ packet
2. Set ping response timeout timer (wait_pingresp:set(3))

This allowed a race where after step 1, execution could switch to the
packet receiver coroutine which might process the PINGRESP before step 2,
causing the timeout timer to be set after the response was already handled.

Now:
1. Set ping response timeout timer first
2. Then send PINGREQ packet

This ensures the timeout timer is always set before any response can be
processed. Also added timeout cancellation on send failure to prevent
false timeout triggers.

The fix ensures proper synchronization between ping requests and response
timeout handling in the coroutine-based MQTT implementation.

Signed-off-by: Jianhui Zhao <zhaojh329@gmail.com>
---
 mqtt.lua | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mqtt.lua b/mqtt.lua
index 99edd02..aaf1c83 100644
--- a/mqtt.lua
+++ b/mqtt.lua
@@ -726,11 +726,13 @@ function M.new(opts)
     end)
 
     o.ping_tmr = time.timer(function(tmr)
+        o.wait_pingresp:set(3)
+
         local ok, err = send_pkt(o, mqtt_packet(PKT_PINGREQ):data())
         if not ok then
+            o.wait_pingresp:cancel()
             on_event(o, 'error', err)
         else
-            o.wait_pingresp:set(3)
             tmr:set(o.opts.keepalive)
         end
     end)
